explanation: The original code used s = [input() for _ in range(n)], which reads n separate lines. In the intended input format the n strings are provided on a single line, so that line is incorrect. I changed it to s = input().split() to read all n strings from one line before sorting and printing the first k.
fixed_code:
n, k = map(int, input().split())
s = input().split()
s.sort()
for i in range(k):
  print(s[i])
